---
import { AlertTriangle } from "lucide-react";

interface Props {
  dashboardUrl?: string;
}

const { dashboardUrl } = Astro.props;
---

<aside
  class="mb-8 rounded-md border border-amber-300 bg-amber-50 p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-amber-900 dark:border-amber-700 dark:bg-amber-950/50 dark:text-amber-100"
  role="note"
>
  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
    <AlertTriangle className="h-5 w-5 mt-0.5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
    <div>
      <strong class="font-semibold">Trust assumptions.</strong>
      Reserves data flows from Apyx's TEE-attested proof-of-solvency feed
      (<a
        href="https://accountable.apyx.fi"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline hover:no-underline"
      >accountable.apyx.fi</a>) — a third-party cryptographic attestation,
      not a PCAOB-firm audit. The custodian holding STRC + cash is unnamed.
      No second independent attestation source exists. The protocol is
      ~3 months old at scale. See {dashboardUrl ? (
        <a href={dashboardUrl} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="underline hover:no-underline">
          the live dashboard's Backing Attestation panel
        </a>
      ) : (
        <span>the Backing Attestation panel on the live dashboard</span>
      )} and the body of this report for what the feed does and doesn't prove.
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>
